  "body": "\r\n***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: Search bar does not appear second (or more) times after pull Home screen down gesture been done while Search bar is present on screen. Please see video and steps of issue below \r\n\r\nNo issue with Android.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSearch bar appears on Home screen after pull-down gesture on iPhone\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nSearch bar does not appear on Home screen second time if pull-down gesture was done before while search bar is shown (on iPhone)\r\nPlease see video of issue here: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1TetB9tHGTfEeQx4679oVM6yMekZb8Lgr/view\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status and create new account\r\n- Join any public chat\r\n- Navigate back to Home screen\r\n- Pull down Home screen so that \"Search\" bar appear\r\n- Pull down Home screen again several times more\r\n- Put cursor in the Search bar (There is a 'Cancel' button should appear next to search bar) \r\n- Tap 'Cancel' button\r\n- Pull down Home screen\r\n \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Develop 0.11, Release 0.10.1\r\n* Operating System: |iOS 12.1.2\r\n\r\n",
